<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,939,1216]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1047,1072]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">Comments.</emphasis>
Only two species of 
<emphasis box="[584,719,1048,1072]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">Lynchiatilla</emphasis>
are known for the state of 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1116,1047,1071]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parana" status="sp. nov.">Paraná</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[1129,1221,1048,1072]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silvai">
<emphasis box="[1129,1144,1049,1072]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1161,1221,1048,1072]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1280,1393,1048,1072]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1280,1295,1049,1072]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1312,1393,1049,1072]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">parana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="7" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
They differ in the color of the head (mostly black in 
<taxonomicName box="[840,933,1084,1108]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silvai">
<emphasis box="[840,933,1084,1108]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">L. silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, red in 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1145,1085,1108]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1031,1145,1085,1108]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">L. parana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1156,1249,1084,1108]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1156,1249,1084,1108]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), scrobal carina (touching the base of the antennal tubercle in 
<taxonomicName box="[668,759,1120,1144]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silvai">
<emphasis box="[668,759,1120,1144]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">L. silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not reaching the base of the antennal tubercle in 
<taxonomicName box="[1324,1436,1121,1144]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,1121,1144]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">L. parana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,240,1156,1180]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,240,1156,1180]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), and the shape of the mesosoma (dorsal face of the propodeum perpendicular to the posterior face (
<figureCitation box="[1360,1427,1156,1180]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1716,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1021,1694]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,1021,1695]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Lynchiatilla spp., females, habitus. 1 – 2. L. parana sp. nov., holotype; 3. L. tacana Casal; 4. L. silvai Casal. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282822/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1412,1427,1156,1180]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName box="[180,290,1193,1216]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[180,290,1193,1216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">L. parana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[297,387,1192,1216]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[297,387,1192,1216]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, dorsal face oblique to the posterior face (
<figureCitation box="[859,926,1191,1215]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1716,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1021,1694]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,1021,1695]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 4. Lynchiatilla spp., females, habitus. 1 – 2. L. parana sp. nov., holotype; 3. L. tacana Casal; 4. L. silvai Casal. Scales = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282822/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[911,926,1191,1215]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName box="[970,1060,1192,1216]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lynchiatilla" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="silvai">
<emphasis box="[970,1060,1192,1216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">L. silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
